# Design System Rules

## Core rule
All layouts and UI must be built using vanilla Bootstrap 5.3 components and utilities. Reach for a Bootstrap utility first; custom CSS is a last resort with a documented reason.

## Spacing
Prefer gap-* on flex/grid parents over margin utilities on children for spacing between siblings. Margin utilities are fine for spacing a block from the page edge.

## Static assets
All static assets live under public/ only. Use kebab-case filenames. Reference with root-absolute paths (/brand/logo.svg). One canonical copy per asset; never duplicate.

## Images
Every image must include the Bootstrap `shadow` utility; no exceptions.
- `<img>` tags: add `shadow` to `className` (combine with other utilities as needed, e.g. `className="img-fluid shadow"`).
- Image placeholders (`role="img"`): add `shadow` alongside any custom layout class.
- Do not duplicate shadow values in custom CSS; use the `shadow` utility only.

## Buttons
Use only: btn-outline-secondary (default), btn-primary (primary CTA), btn-outline-success, btn-outline-warning, btn-outline-danger, btn-outline-info.
Never use: solid btn-secondary/success/warning/danger/info, btn-outline-primary, btn-dark, btn-light.

## Banned Bootstrap utilities
Never use: fs-1 through fs-6, fw-* utilities, display-1 through display-6, bg-dark, bg-light, text-dark, text-light, rounded-pill, and all -dark/-light variants.
Use instead: bg-body, bg-body-secondary, text-body, text-muted.
For type scale: use h1–h6 elements, lead, small; not font size utilities.
Never apply the `small` class to heading elements (`h1`–`h6`); use the correct heading level for size instead.

## Banned CSS patterns
- No inline style={{}} props
- No hardcoded hex colors anywhere
- No custom design tokens (--color-*, --font-*, etc.); use --bs-* variables only
- No component-level CSS files
- No CSS modules, styled-components, or CSS-in-JS
- No custom margin/padding/flex rules in CSS; use Bootstrap utilities
- No <strong> or <b> for font weight
- No ::-webkit-scrollbar rules

## Copy
Never use the em dash (`—`, U+2014) in user-visible website copy. This includes page text, `<title>` and meta descriptions, Open Graph tags, aria-labels, alt text, and button/link labels.

Use instead:
- Pipe (`|`) to separate title segments (e.g. `Voicebox | Maxim Sokolov`)
- Colon, comma, or period for label–detail pairs (e.g. `Lead: Geist sans-serif, body scale.`)
- Hyphen-minus (`-`) for compound modifiers when a dash is needed (e.g. `UX/UI Designer & Engineer`)

En dashes (`–`) are allowed only for numeric ranges (e.g. `150–160 chars`).

## Custom CSS
Lives in shared/design/_extensions.scss only. Every custom rule needs a comment explaining why Bootstrap can't handle it.

## Before writing code
Always list files you plan to create, ask clarifying questions, and surface ambiguities before writing any code.
